@page "/bootstrap5"
<PageTitle>Bootstrap 5 - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1>Bootstrap 5</h1>

<main class="documentation">

    <section class="card">

        <h2>Overview</h2>

        <p class="subtitle">
            Use Saascade components with Bootstrap 5's vanilla CSS classes.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h3>Setup</h3>

        <pre><code>builder.Services.AddSingleton&lt;IDesignSystem&gt;(DesignSystems.Bootstrap5.VanillaBootstrap5);</code></pre>

        <p>
            The <code>VanillaBootstrap5DesignSystem</code> maps each component to standard
            Bootstrap 5 class names — <code>card</code>, <code>btn</code>, <code>navbar</code>, etc.
        </p>

    </section>

    <section class="card">

        <h2>Stylesheet References</h2>

        <p>
            The design system provides Bootstrap's CDN stylesheet automatically via
            <code>GetStylesheetReferences()</code>. Include the
            <code>&lt;DesignSystemStylesheetReferences /&gt;</code> component in your
            <code>index.html</code> or layout.
        </p>

    </section>

</main>
